🔤 Python Syntax Basics

✔ No semicolons required
✔ Easy indentation
✔ Readable code structure

---

💻 Variables Example

```python id="variable_example"
name = "Saakshi"
age = 22

print(name)
print(age)
```

---

📌 Rules for Variable Names

✔ Can contain letters, numbers, `_`
✔ Cannot start with a number
✔ Case-sensitive

---

🔢 Basic Data Types

| Data Type | Example    |
| --------- | ---------- |
| Integer   | `10`       |
| Float     | `3.14`     |
| String    | `"Python"` |
| Boolean   | `True`     |

---

💻 Data Type Example

```python id="datatype_example"
x = 10
pi = 3.14
language = "Python"
is_fun = True

print(type(x))
print(type(pi))
print(type(language))
print(type(is_fun))
```

---

🔧 Taking User Input

```python id="input_example"
name = input("Enter your name: ")

print("Welcome", name)
```

---

➕ Basic Operators

| Operator | Meaning        |
| -------- | -------------- |
| `+`      | Addition       |
| `-`      | Subtraction    |
